'A number of occasions and a number of opportunities to diagnose and successfully treat his condition were missed,' he said.

Stockport NHS Foundation Trust has since apologised and carried out an investigation.

A spokesman said improvements had been made at the hospital, including the introduction of an electronic system to record patient details.

'It is clear that we missed important opportunities in the care of Brian Holland and for that we are very sorry,' he added.

